l_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1320:"<p>It has come to our attention that there&#8217;s a security vulnerability in older Mantra version.</p>\n<h3>The affected versions are <strong>1.7.7 to 1.8.9.1. </strong>No other versions are affected.<strong><br />\n</strong></h3>\n<h3>If you are running any of these versions, <strong>please update as soon as possible.</strong></h3>\n<p>The vulnerability could allow an attacker to upload a malformed image file in the mantra/uploads folder and potentially execute arbitrary code on the server.</p>\n<p>If you are unable to update due to various modifications/customizations you have performed on the theme. delete the <strong>mantra/admin/upload-file.php</strong> file to remove the vulnerability. (Note that this will prevent you from changing your favicon image in the future)</p>\n<p>In both cases, also check the files in mantra/uploads folder and make sure your installation hasn&#8217;t been compromised. If you find any suspicious files:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;">non-image files</span></li>\n<li>image files which you do not remember to have uploaded</li>\n<li>weirdly named image files</li>\n<li>image files with double extensions</li>\n</ul>\n<p>delete them immediately, and check your entire hosting account / server to make sure no other files have been compromised.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:106:"http://www.cryoutcreations.eu/wordpress-themes/mantra/security-vulnerability-in-older-mantra-versions/feed";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1: